Real Madrid's Kaka Approached by Corinthians in Brazil, Folha Reports

-- B y   F r a n c i s c o   M a r c e l i n o
-- 
2011-02-17T14:49:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-17/real-madrid-s-kaka-approached-by-corinthians-in-brazil-folha-reports.html
  Brazil ’s SC Corinthians Paulista
approached Real Madrid’s midfielder Kaka to check whether he
would agree to hear a proposal from the Sao Paulo-based soccer
team,  Folha de S.Paulo  reported, without saying how it obtained
the information.  Kaka said he is unlikely to leave Real Madrid at the
moment, according to the newspaper’s columnist Monica Bergamo.  Corinthians is seeking a player to replace striker Ronaldo,
who announced his retirement from soccer on Feb. 14, Folha said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Francisco Marcelino in  Sao Paulo  at 
 mdeoliveira@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
